---
// DAY-166. Landing page.
//
// Reading order matches the sales argument:
//
//   1. Hero           — emotional + visual. "Your day is scattered →
//                       Dayseam → one report." Scroll-driven black
//                       hole animation; reduced-motion users get a
//                       three-panel static equivalent.
//
//   2. How it works   — rational. Three labelled steps so anyone who
//                       needed a little more context after the hero
//                       gets it here without leaving the page.
//
//   3. Connector grid — concrete. Shows exactly what plugs in today
//                       (five) and what's on deck (five), by name,
//                       with each tool's own brand colour + mark.
//
//   4. Trust strip    — preempts the four things a local-first app's
//                       audience always asks ("where is my data?
//                       is there an account? what's with my tokens?
//                       what do you phone home?"), each one-sentence
//                       and cross-referenced to docs/privacy-security.md
//                       for the detailed answer.
//
//   5. Download CTA   — single conversion surface. Links to
//                       /releases/latest so it never advertises a
//                       stale version.
//
// Notes on the hero island:
//
//   The Hero component is a React island hydrated with
//   `client:only="react"`. Two reasons:
//     - `client:load` would try to SSR the component. `framer-motion`
//       ships browser-only code in `useScroll` / `MotionValue` that
//       does not play nicely with Astro's static build.
//     - `client:visible` would delay hydration until the section
//       intersects the viewport, but the section IS the viewport on
//       first paint, so there's no latency win.
//   `client:only="react"` renders nothing on the server and hydrates
//   as soon as JS loads — cheapest correct option.
//
//   Because the hero island renders nothing server-side, the page's
//   only <h1> and the product pitch would be missing from the static
//   HTML. That breaks three things at once:
//     1. Crawlers / previewers that don't execute JS (rare but real)
//        see a page with no headline, skipping straight to "Three
//        steps. No meetings about meetings" (an <h2>).
//     2. Visitors with JS disabled — or with a failed JS load because
//        of an ad-blocker / CSP mismatch / network drop between the
//        HTML and the island bundle — see the same empty hero frame.
//     3. The document outline becomes h2-only, which is a WCAG 2.4.6
//        regression on the landing page.
//
//   The <noscript> block below ships a server-rendered h1 + pitch +
//   three-step summary using the same copy as `HeroStatic`. It's
//   hidden when JS is running (browsers remove <noscript> contents
//   from the accessibility tree when scripting is enabled), so the
//   animated hero remains the primary experience. The static copy
//   deliberately lives here rather than being extracted into a
//   separate Astro component because it is only four short blocks
//   and the one caller is this file — a component would just add
//   indirection.
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero";
import HowItWorks from "../components/HowItWorks.astro";
import ConnectorGrid from "../components/ConnectorGrid.astro";
import TrustStrip from "../components/TrustStrip.astro";
import DownloadCTA from "../components/DownloadCTA.astro";
---

<Base>
  <noscript>
    <section
      class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20"
      aria-label="How Dayseam works"
    >
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <h1
          class="text-balance text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-zinc-50 sm:text-5xl"
        >
          The report of your day, written from evidence
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-balance text-lg text-zinc-400">
          Dayseam collects what you actually did across GitHub, GitLab, Jira,
          Confluence, and your local repos, then stitches it into an editable
          Markdown report, locally, with no account and no telemetry
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-sm text-zinc-500">
          This page has an interactive hero that needs JavaScript to render.
          <a href="#how-it-works" class="underline hover:text-zinc-300">
            Skip to how it works
          </a>
          .
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </noscript>
  <Hero client:only="react" />
  <HowItWorks />
  <ConnectorGrid />
  <TrustStrip />
  <DownloadCTA />
</Base>
